A given opinion may deal with subjective matters in which there is no conclusive finding, or it may deal with facts which are sought to be disputed by the logical fallacy that one is entitled to their opinions.

Distinguishing fact from opinion is that facts are verifiable, i.e. can be agreed to by the consensus of experts. An example is: "United States of America was involved in the Vietnam War," versus "United States of America was right to get involved in the Vietnam War". An opinion may be supported by facts and principles, in which case it becomes an argument.

Different people may draw opposing conclusions (opinions) even if they agree on the same set of facts. Opinions rarely change without new arguments being presented. It can be reasoned that one opinion is better supported by the facts than another, by analyzing the supporting arguments.[1]

In casual use, the term opinion may be the result of a person's perspective, understanding, particular feelings, beliefs, and desires.

column204: How to add contacts on TenFour
column205:
Hi Walter, 
 How is it going? I hope you are enjoying using TenFour. 
 I promised to guide you on how to add contacts to your TenFour instance. There are three ways to do this.Â  
 - You can add an individual by clicking the +Add icon.Fill out the user's necessary details ie Name, phone number, email address, address and their permissions, which will you will click on 'roles' to do that. 
 [Image "image.png"] - You can add multiple people by importing contacts via csv file. Download the sample csv file and fill out the user's contact information provided. Upload the file, match your data and import your contact to your organization. 
 [Image "image.png"] - For larger organizations you can add via Active directory(Ldap).Click Active directory, slide toggle to enable ldap sync and fill in the settings as instructed. 
 [Image "image.png"] Here is a link to help your further. https://www.tenfour.org/support/adding-users 
 The next tip will be to how to send and reply to check-ins. 
 Click reply if you have any questions i'll be happy to help you in way you need. 
 Kind Regards, 
 Cecilia Hinga

 For you to reach out to your team on any device when its most important all you need to do is send a "check-in" and get fast answers on the question "Are you ok?". 
 - All you need to do is, click on Check-in, then create. Â  
 [Image "image.png"] - Compose your message.Â  
 [Image "image.png"] - Select channels via which to send out your check-in, add people to send your check-in to and click send.

column204: Tips to get started with TestRail
column205:
Hello Walter,

I wanted to send you some tips to get the most out of TestRail to help you
make your test management and testing efforts more efficient:

1. TestRail Video Tour
======================

Watch our 1-hour TestRail training video course to learn more about
TestRail's major benefits and features, best practices and recommendations,
as well as TestRail's JIRA and bug tracker integration.

http://www.gurock.com/testrail/videos/introduction-projects/


2. Invite Your Team to TestRail
===============================

You can also invite your team to your TestRail trial! To do this, simply
select Administration > Users & Roles from your TestRail account to add and
invite additional team members. Get the most out of your trial by testing
TestRail with your team.

http://docs.gurock.com/testrail-faq/usage-add-users


3. JIRA & Bug Tracker Integration
=================================

TestRail is the only test management tool that easily integrates with any
JIRA edition and version, including JIRA Cloud! TestRail can also be used
and integrated with many other tools such as FogBugz, Redmine, Bugzilla,
Rally and more.

http://docs.gurock.com/testrail-integration/start


4. Managing Separate Test Steps
===============================

Did you know that you can also manage and pass/fail separate test steps in
TestRail? If you prefer this over TestRail's default Steps and Expected
Result fields, you can follow the below documentation link to adjust
TestRail's flexible custom fields for separate test steps.

http://docs.gurock.com/testrail-faq/config-steps


If there's anything else you need from us at the moment or if you or your
team have any questions, just let us know!

Kind regards,
Gurock Team

-- 
Customer Success
Gurock Software GmbH
http://www.gurock.com/

column204: How to add contacts on TenFour
column205:
Hi Walter, 
 How is it going? I hope you are enjoying using TenFour. 
 I promised to guide you on how to add contacts to your TenFour instance. There are three ways to do this.Â  
 - You can add an individual by clicking the +Add icon.Fill out the user's necessary details ie Name, phone number, email address, address and their permissions, which will you will click on 'roles' to do that. 
 [Image "image.png"] - You can add multiple people by importing contacts via csv file. Download the sample csv file and fill out the user's contact information provided. Upload the file, match your data and import your contact to your organization. 
 [Image "image.png"] - For larger organizations you can add via Active directory(Ldap).Click Active directory, slide toggle to enable ldap sync and fill in the settings as instructed. 
 [Image "image.png"] Here is a link to help your further. https://www.tenfour.org/support/adding-users 
 The next tip will be to how to send and reply to check-ins. 
 Click reply if you have any questions i'll be happy to help you in way you need. 
 Kind Regards, 
 Cecilia Hinga

column204: 7 Reasons why testing teams switch to TestRail
column205:
Hello Walter,

Have you found TestRail useful so far? Many teams switch to TestRail from
various tools every week and I thought it would be helpful to provide a
quick list of some of the reasons why teams switch to TestRail (based on
actual customer feedback we regularly receive):

1. Increased productivity: we spend a lot of time optimizing every aspect of
TestRail's user experience to make testing teams more efficient. Don't waste
time with slow apps, cumbersome interfaces or complicated tools! Our
customers regularly tell us that TestRail's fast interface and rich
application structure helps them get more done compared to other tools they
tried. Benefit from TestRail's modern web interface with drag&drop support,
context-aware navigation and flexible customization options.

2. Rich capabilities: easily manage projects, milestones, test cases and
runs with TestRail's rich application structure. Reuse test cases, execute
tests against configurations (such as OS, mobile devices or browsers) and
organize, filter & group your tests. And to work with your team or
customers, easily define user groups, manage roles and permissions and
assign tests with personalized to-do lists. TestRail also comes with
critical functionality many tools don't have: easily archive your test runs
so they aren't affected by changed, moved or deleted test cases, or directly
set up multiple project baselines.

3. JIRA & bug tracker integration: we specifically designed TestRail to
integrate with JIRA and many other issue & bug tracking tools, including
JIRA Cloud! So with TestRail you can directly push bug reports to your
favorite tool, link test results, look up the issue status from TestRail and
generate detailed coverage reports. And unlike many other tools, there's no
need to run error-prone synchronizations or install any add-ons in your
issue tracker with TestRail. TestRail also directly integrates with
requirements, test automation, authentication systems and more!

4. Flexible customizations: we built TestRail so teams can easily adjust it
for their needs: define custom fields, change user roles, benefit from our
unique UI scripts and customize TestRail's issue tracker and authentication
integration when you need it. TestRail is the most flexible test management
tool available and our customers use it to manage testing for all kinds of
projects, including blockbuster games, leading websites, consumer and
medical devices, defense projects, popular mobile apps and complex IT
systems.

5. Deep reporting: TestRail comes with advanced reporting options, including
real-time statistics and rich built-in report templates. Easily compare test
results across runs and platforms, follow the testing progress with unique
time forecasts, generate coverage reports and create status reports for
management and customers. And best of all, all reports can be scheduled to
be generated and forwarded automatically.

6. Scales with your needs: we designed and built TestRail to scale well for
teams and projects of all sizes. TestRail is used and loved by one-man
shops, growing startups, IT departments, product companies as well as
enterprise teams with 1000+ testers. Whether you are using agile methods, a
traditional approach or work on custom projects: TestRail works great out of
the box. And unlike other tools that get slow or cumbersome to use once you
start managing larger number of tests, TestRail scales well with both our
cloud and on-premise editions.

7. Simple pricing & great service: providing fast, friendly and accurate
support is one of our main differentiators. Just email us if you have any
questions! TestRail is also very competitively priced. But did you know that
many other tools charge extra for critical features like reporting or API
access? Or that you often need to purchase licenses for all your JIRA or bug
tracker users, even if they don't need access to test management? With
TestRail you pay a single low price for all our features and you only pay
for users who actually use TestRail.

If there's anything else you need from us at the moment or if you have any
questions, just let me know!

Kind regards,
Gurock Team

-- 
Customer Success
Gurock Software GmbH
http://www.gurock.com/

column204: How successful testing teams use TestRail
column205:
Hello Walter,

I wanted to share some quick tips on how other successful teams use TestRail
to manage their testing efforts. TestRail is used by thousands of teams from
many different industries now, ranging from one-man shops over growing
startups to huge enterprise teams with 1000+ testers:

http://www.gurock.com/testrail/customers/

But even with the diversity of projects, there's a common set of aspects
successful and highly-effective teams follow when using TestRail:

1. Start with a simple project structure and simple tests:
http://www.gurock.com/testrail/videos/introduction-projects/

2. Integrate TestRail with your issue/bug tracker:
http://www.gurock.com/testrail/tour/testing-integration/

3. Get the whole team on board by inviting them or sharing reports: 
http://docs.gurock.com/testrail-faq/usage-add-users

4. Migrate your existing test cases to TestRail:
http://docs.gurock.com/testrail-admin/migration-introduction

5. Adjust TestRail for your needs via custom fields:
http://docs.gurock.com/testrail-userguide/howto-fields

6. Reuse existing test cases instead of duplicating them:
http://www.gurock.com/testrail/videos/suites-test-cases/

7. Take advantage of test plans with configurations:
http://www.gurock.com/testrail/videos/test-plans-configurations/

8. Get familiar with TestRail's reporting system:
http://www.gurock.com/testrail/tour/test-reporting-metrics/

9. Do you manage requirements? Integrate and report on them:
http://docs.gurock.com/testrail-integration/references-introduction

10. Use TestRail's API to automate and integrate tests:
http://docs.gurock.com/testrail-api2/

Have you found TestRail useful for your team so far? And is there anything
else you need from us at the moment? We are happy to help and you can simply
reply to this email if you have any questions.

Kind regards,
Gurock Team

-- 
Customer Success
Gurock Software GmbH
http://www.gurock.com/


Unsubscribe from trial emails:
http://www.gurock.com/go/canceltrtrial/ef99ef4c4a26706cd00d3bf78b22fa88/

Hi there, 
 I noticed you created an Ushahidi deployment a few days ago. I'm just getting in touch to see how Ushahidi is working out for you.

These tutorials will help you understand the focal plane!

THE FOCAL PLANE!
The one question I'm asked about regularly is "How are you getting all your subjects sharp when shooting wide open because when I do it there's always someone out of focus"!!
Here's an overview of how it's achieved
1. We need to remember that a camera can only focus at a single point and in one single plane of focus. Imagine that there's an invisible wall in front of your family. The aim is to get all your subjects to touch their noses against that invisible wall!
2. The focal plane (Invisible wall) also has depth! The longer the lens the wider the focal plane which in turn gives you some wiggle room for subjects in a group making it easier to have everyone in focus while giving you that creamy background too!
3. You can narrow your aperture so instead of e,g f2 you could shoot at f2.8, f4...etc but this is the last resort!

Below is a selection of tutorials where I cover the subject of the focal plane in detail!

We'll be welcoming a new layout of the site and rebranding!


** NEW WEBSITE LAUNCH
------------------------------------------------------------
You're about to be welcomed to Photo Education By Daniel!

You may or may not have heard the news but we're preparing to launch our new site on the 1st of March! The launch brings a new site layout and new website address!
We've been hard at work getting everything in place and making sure it all works as normal. The new site will still be a work in progress as we try to add new features but we've tried to make the site easier to navigate and find the tutorials you need.
I will be releasing many new tutorials in the coming days after the launch as I held them back from the current system we're on so you can expect plenty!
There's a redesign of the blog too which will be seeing lots of goodies to read about and videos to watch (There's been a few already loaded on the current site but not many folks have seen them)

All in all its a new year for us and couldn't come at a better time! I had to think about the rebrand due to want happened last year when we lost all our social media and I still have domains locked in the inaccessible business pages where we had Shoot Create Captivate - This will now become the "tagline"

I want to take this opportunity to thank you all for the amazing support and kind words shared in the many reviews and on social media! It means so much especially when you're pouring your heart and soul into it! I've got more to share and am excited to use this new platform to be able to pass on every bit of knowledge to you!

PLEASE NOTE:
The current website address you've bookmarked will automatically redirect to the new site so you don't need to do anything and your logins and passwords will remain unchanged
THERE WILL BE A FEW HOURS OF OUTAGE and you will likely see an under-construction page / coming soon!
We've scheduled the switchover during the course of the 1st of March on the UK TIME ZONE

Have an awesome week and see you on the new site! I'm really excited to share all the new tutorials!

Happy shooting and learning

Daniel and Eva
The new domain will be
www.photoeducationbydaniel.com
